      "longTitle": "EXHIBIT B: The Raid at Millbrook",
      "interactionPrompt": "Look at the scene. Who is in control of this land?",
      "tabs": {
        "primary": {
          "body": "## **FIRE VS. LAW**\n\nThe RCMP arrived at Leo's Trading Post at 9:00 AM. They had a warrant to seize the cannabis. \n\nThey stopped when they saw the **Sacred Fire**.\n\n**WHY IT MATTERS:**\nThe community lit a fire in the doorway. In Mi'kmaw culture, this is a sacred space. If the police stepped over the fire, they would be disrespecting the culture and escalating the conflict.\n\n**THE BLOCKADE:**\nLook at the background. Pickup trucks have blocked the road. The community is saying: \"This is our land. Your rules stop at the highway.\" The police are frozen.",
          "image": "http://dwaugh-edsim.github.io/projectimages/leo-sitroom2/images/rcmp-protest-ai.jpg",
          "credit": "Standoff at the Sacred Fire"
        },
        "legal": {
          "body": "## **THE BAND COUNCIL RESOLUTION (BCR)**\n\nLeo taped this document to his front door. It is a law passed by the Chief and Council.\n\n**WHAT IT SAYS:**\nIt declares that the Province has no right to enforce cannabis laws on the reserve. It says the RCMP are **Trespassing**.\n\n**THE CONFLICT:**\n* **The Province** has a Search Warrant (Provincial Law).\n* **The Band** has a Resolution (Indigenous Law).\n\n**THE PROBLEM:**\nWhich paper is more powerful? The Supreme Court hasn't fully decided yet. You have to decide which law applies here.",
          "image": "http://dwaugh-edsim.github.io/projectimages/leo-sitroom2/images/band-door-AI.jpg",
          "credit": "Band Council Resolution (BCR)"
        },
        "intel": {
          "body": "## **THE LAB REPORT**\n\n**EVIDENCE:** Product Safety\n\nThe Government claims this raid is about **Public Safety**. They say illegal weed is dangerous because it might have mold or chemicals.\n\n**THE TRUTH:**\nWe tested Leo's product. Look at the report.\n* **Pesticides:** None.\n* **Mold:** None.\n* **Quality:** High.\n\n**ANALYSIS:**\nLeo runs a clean shop. He checks IDs. He tests his product. If his shop is safe, why did they raid him? Is it really about safety, or is it about **Money** (Taxes)?",
          "image": "http://dwaugh-edsim.github.io/projectimages/leo-sitroom2/images/leo-test-report.jpg",
          "credit": "Forensic Lab Report"
        }
