        "primary": {
          "body": "## **THE GOVERNMENT'S CASE**\n\nThe Justice Minister speaks to the press. He looks serious.\n\n**HIS MESSAGE:**\n\"We respect the Treaties. But we also have to follow the law. The Supreme Court has said that Treaty Rights are not unlimited.\n\nWe have a new court ruling called **R. v. Googoo**. A judge decided last year that cannabis is NOT protected by the Treaty because the Mi'kmaq didn't use it in 1750. \n\nLeo Francis is breaking the law. We will enforce it.\"\n\n**THE TRAP:**\nThe Government is using the **\"Frozen Rights\"** argument. They are trying to freeze Leo's rights in the past.",
