        "legal": {
          "body": "## **THE GOOGOO CASE**\n\n**THE PRECEDENT:** *R. v. Googoo (2024)*\n\nThis is the biggest problem for Leo. In a similar case last year, the judge said **Guilty**.\n\n**WHY?**\nThe judge said there was no \"historical continuity.\" Since cannabis wasn't here in 1752, the Treaty doesn't cover it.\n\n**YOUR JOB:**\nCan you find a difference between Leo's case and the *Googoo* case? \n* Leo tests his products (Safe).\n* The shop in *Googoo* might not have been safe.\n* Maybe Leo's case is different because he is **Self-Regulated**.",
          "image": "http://dwaugh-edsim.github.io/projectimages/leo-sitroom2/images/googoo-ai.jpg",
          "credit": "The Googoo Decision Summary"
        },
        "intel": {
          "body": "## **THE EMPTY BOX**\n\n**CONCEPT:** The Crown's Theory\n\nLook at the image of the box with the question mark. This is how the Province sees Indigenous rights.\n\n**THE IDEA:**\nThey believe the \"Box of Rights\" is empty. They believe Indigenous people have no commercial rights unless the Government grants them permission.\n\n**THE RISK:**\nIf you agree with the Crown, you are saying that the Treaty of 1752 is just a piece of paper with no power today.",
          "image": "http://dwaugh-edsim.github.io/projectimages/leo-sitroom2/images/magicbox-1-ai.jpg",
