      "longTitle": "EXHIBIT E: The Sparrow Test",
      "interactionPrompt": "Use the Checklist. Is the Government allowed to break the Treaty?",
      "tabs": {
        "primary": {
          "body": "## **THE MARSHALL LEGACY**\n\nThis case reminds everyone of **Donald Marshall Jr.**\n\nIn 1999, he was arrested for catching eels. The Supreme Court ruled he was innocent because he had a Treaty Right to a **\"Moderate Livelihood\"** (enough money to live on).\n\n**THE QUESTION:**\nDoes \"Moderate Livelihood\" apply to cannabis?\n\n**THE LIVING TREE:**\nIndigenous lawyers argue the Treaty is like a tree. It grows. \n* In 1750, they traded furs.\n* In 1990, they traded fish.\n* In 2025, they trade cannabis.\n\nIf you agree with Leo, you are letting the tree grow. If you agree with the Crown, you are cutting it back.",
          "image": "http://dwaugh-edsim.github.io/projectimages/leo-sitroom2/images/Supreme_Court_of_Nova_Scotia_in_2018-Wikimedia.jpg",
          "credit": "Supreme Court of Nova Scotia"
        },
        "legal": {
          "body": "## **THE SPARROW CHECKLIST**\n\nJudges use a tool called the **Sparrow Test** to decide these cases. Follow the steps:\n\n**STEP 1: Is there a Right?**\n(Yes. The Treaty of 1752 exists).\n\n**STEP 2: Did the Government break the Right?**\n(Yes. They raided the shop and took the goods).\n\n**STEP 3: Was there a GOOD REASON?**\nThis is the hard part. The Government says the reason is **\"Public Safety.\"**\n\n**STEP 4: Did they do it gently?**\nThis is called \"Minimal Impairment.\" Could the police have just *inspected* Leo's shop instead of shutting it down? If they used too much force, the raid was illegal.",
          "image": "http://dwaugh-edsim.github.io/projectimages/leo-sitroom2/images/sparrow-1-ai.jpg",
          "credit": "The Sparrow Test"
        },
        "intel": {
          "body": "## **WHAT IS 'MODERATE'?**\n\n**EVIDENCE:** Leo's Financials\n\nThe Crown says Leo is making too much money. They say \"Moderate Livelihood\" means just enough to buy food—poverty level.\n\n**THE REALITY:**\nWe looked at Leo's books. \n* He supports his family.\n* He pays for heating oil for Elders.\n* He sponsors the local hockey team.\n\n**DECISION:**\nIs this \"getting rich\"? Or is this supporting a community? The definition of \"Moderate\" is up to you.",
          "image": "http://dwaugh-edsim.github.io/projectimages/leo-sitroom2/images/marshall-1.jpg",
          "credit": "The Marshall Case Files"
        }
